### Logic Apps Standard - Feature Toggle Spike
### Sample requests. Replace {host} with your local func host (default http://localhost:7071)
### and {key} with the workflow's SAS signature from the trigger URL shown in VS Code.
### When running locally with the Azure Logic Apps (Standard) extension, the trigger URL
### is: http://localhost:7071/api/<workflow-name>/triggers/<trigger-name>/invoke?api-version=2022-05-01&sp=...&sv=...&sig=...

@host = http://localhost:7071

### 01 - App Settings toggle (new pricing on => 10% promo; flip FeatureFlag_NewPricingEngine in local.settings.json)
POST {{host}}/api/01-appsettings-toggle/triggers/When_an_order_is_received/invoke?api-version=2022-05-01
Content-Type: application/json

{ "orderId": "ORD-1001", "amount": 200 }

### 02 - Azure App Configuration toggle (requires a real AppConfig store + managed identity; see README)
POST {{host}}/api/02-appconfiguration-toggle/triggers/When_a_shipment_is_requested/invoke?api-version=2022-05-01
Content-Type: application/json

{ "shipmentId": "SHP-77", "destination": "Seattle" }

### 03 - Parameters file toggle (email on/off via FeatureFlag_SendEmailNotifications)
POST {{host}}/api/03-parameters-file-toggle/triggers/When_an_invoice_is_created/invoke?api-version=2022-05-01
Content-Type: application/json

{ "invoiceId": "INV-555", "customerEmail": "test@example.com" }

### 04a - Inline control-flow: version routing (set Routing_FulfillmentVersion = legacy | v2 | canary)
POST {{host}}/api/04-inline-controlflow-toggle/triggers/When_fulfillment_is_requested/invoke?api-version=2022-05-01
Content-Type: application/json

{ "orderId": "ORD-2002" }

### 04b - Inline control-flow: mock branch
POST {{host}}/api/04-inline-controlflow-toggle/triggers/When_fulfillment_is_requested/invoke?api-version=2022-05-01
Content-Type: application/json

{ "orderId": "ORD-2003", "useMock": true }
